## Glossary

### Component Terms

**Variant** - A style variation of a component (e.g., `primary`, `success`, `danger`, `ghost`). Each component supports different variants for different use cases.

**Size** - Component size modifier. Common sizes include `sm` (small), `md` (medium, default), `lg` (large), and `xl` (extra large).

**Include** - Jekyll/Liquid syntax for including reusable component templates. All CFL components use the `{% raw %}{% include components/... %}{% endraw %}` pattern.

**Modifier** - CSS class suffix that changes component appearance or behavior (e.g., `--primary`, `--striped`, `--hoverable`). Modifiers follow the BEM naming convention.

**Block** - A boolean parameter that makes buttons span full width of their container.

**Dot** - A small status indicator that appears on badges and avatars to show state (online, offline, away).

**Pulse** - An animated pulsing effect applied to badges and status indicators to draw attention.

**Holographic** - A rainbow gradient animation effect available on buttons, text, borders, and containers using classes like `.cfl-holo`, `.cfl-holo-text`, `.cfl-holo-border`.

**Skeleton** - A loading placeholder that mimics the shape of content while data loads.

**Toast** - A temporary notification that appears briefly, typically triggered by user actions.

### CSS Classes

**`.cfl-*`** - All CFL component classes are prefixed with `cfl-` to avoid conflicts with other stylesheets.

**`.showcase-*`** - Utility classes specific to this showcase page for layout and demonstration purposes.

**`.cfl-btn--*`** - Button modifier classes (e.g., `--primary`, `--rainbow`, `--bouncy`).

**`.cfl-table--*`** - Table modifier classes (e.g., `--striped`, `--hoverable`, `--compact`).

### Common Parameters

- **`text`** - Text content displayed in the component
- **`href`** - URL for links and buttons
- **`variant`** - Style variant name
- **`size`** - Size modifier
- **`icon`** / **`icon_right`** - Emoji or icon to display
- **`label`** - Descriptive text label
- **`value`** - Numeric or string value
- **`checked`** - Boolean for toggles and checkboxes
- **`disabled`** - Boolean to disable interaction
- **`title`** / **`body`** - Content for alerts and callouts

See the [Components Documentation](/wiki/components) for full API reference.
